"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-04-paris-2024-olympics-troost-ekong-lauds-amazing-dtigress-win-over-canada\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Super Eagles captain William Troost-Ekong has heaped plaudits on the D'Tigress following the team's remarkable victory over Canada.  Rena Wakama's side sealed a place in the quarter-finals of the women's basketball event following a hard-earned 79-70 victory over world number five Canada.  D'Tigress are the first African team, male or female, to reach the quarter-finals of Olympic basketball.  Troost-Ekong took to the social media to celebrate the team's for the historic feat.  \\\"Amazing achievement let us go all the way!, he wrote on X.  The African champions will hope to go a step further by making it to the semi-finals.    Chilekwu announces departure from Enyimba  We should have defeated Man Utd more than 3-0 - Liverpool manager, Arne Slot  D'Tigress maintain 8th position in latest FIBA women's rankings  FIBA WWCQ: D'Tigress star Macaulay named in All-Star team  D'Tigress captain Ogoke retires from national team  FG fulfils pledge to D'Tigress for winning 2025 FIBA Women's Afrobasket  2026 FIBA World Cup Qualifiers: D'Tigress rally to 101-84 victory over Philippines  FIBA WWQ 2026: Gallant D'Tigress fall 77-60 to Korea  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"